      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear that, but people always point to the psychometric data itself. like, even if environment plays a role, there are still massive gaps in the actual test results that follow certain patterns. can u look into the specific arguments made by researchers who believe these gaps have a genetic component? like the stuff from the bell curve era or similar studies? just wanna see both sides of the debate for my work.",
