      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Proponents of genetic explanations often focus on heritability studies, suggesting that observed cognitive differences within populations can have a genetic underpinnings. These arguments often leverage twin or adoption studies, interpreting correlations in test scores as evidence of genetic influence. Critics counter that many of these analyses do not sufficiently control for confounding environmental variables or the distinct ways cultural background interacts with standardized testing. Ultimately, those arguing for a genetic component often push for more rigidly defined genetic markers, while others emphasize the complexity of gene-environment interaction.",
