      "content": "right, but if you look at the actual data points, some of those studies claim that the gaps are too large to be explained by just poverty or schooling alone. i've seen people arguing that there's a fundamental biological hierarchy being shown in the data. can u be more specific about those findings? like, what are the actual claims made about the differences in cognitive abilities between specific groups that these researchers point to? i want to get a clear picture of what they are actually saying.",
